time required: 35 minutes
---

Peel and then finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Peel the @carrot{1}(peeled) and cut into carrot sticks, then thinly slice those sticks widthways to make flat squares.

Cut the @vine tomatoes{2} in half and use a #teaspoon{} to remove the seeds and discard. Roughly chop the tomato flesh.

Put @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over a medium heat. Once hot add the @97% pork sausages{4} and brown them off on all sides for about ~{4%minutes}.

Remove the sausages from the pan and add the onions and carrots. Gently cook until soft over a medium heat for about ~{5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for a further ~{2%minutes}.

Return the sausages to the pan along with the drained @organic lentils{1%can}. Add the @wholegrain mustard{1%tsp}, half the @chicken stock{1/2%stock cube} and @water{100%ml}. Add the @thyme{2%sprigs} and tomatoes and cook on a medium-low heat for ~{20%minutes}. Season with @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{a few grinds}.

Wash the @spring greens{1}(washed and stalks removed) and roughly tear the leaves, discarding any tough parts. Heat @olive oil{2%tsp} in a #medium sized pot{} on medium-low heat. Once hot add the greens, @salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{} and cover with a lid and cook for ~{5%minutes}.

> The water from washing the greens will be enough to cook the leaves.

Taste everything for seasoning and add salt and pepper if necessary. Check the greens are soft enough to eat and if you have some @?butter{1%knob} you can add a knob as a decadent touch! Serve the casserole on your plates, sprinkle over some @flat leaf parsley{}(chopped), add the greens to the side and enjoy!